<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-B25C7254-5B95-4D3F-A72E-D9FD39C66AF3" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-B25C7254-5B95-4D3F-A72E-D9FD39C66AF3" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Configure the network</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-14F5A707-938B-4294-9E2F-EAD5C535D52F"><p class="- topic/p ">At installation, the printer is connected to the network and connectivity settings are made. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If necessary, you can change the network configuration settings on the user panel. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-67A7F7AC-708F-4201-BE94-C7F7868E5C14" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Network overview</title><table id="d14126e25" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="291.75pt" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="221.50pt" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connection via 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer receives jobs from the RIP workstation 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">RAW TCP/IP (port 9100) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer connects via the internet with the back office 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">HTTPS (port 443) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer connects to the mail server for password recovery and to inform the administrator of security updates and new software versions.
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">SMTP (port 25 by default, can be changed) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">You can access the settings editor 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">HTTP (port 80) or HTTPS (port 443 by default, can be changed) 
</p><note id="d14126e66" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">HTTPS requires a valid certificate. 
</p></note></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><steps id="GUID-A0CD2416-0B3D-4763-B58A-EA6018BF2080" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_CCD40DF3BDB4457C8844C7EE0276E2BA" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel, tap on the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="SYSTEM_ID" class="- topic/text ">System</text></uicontrol> icon on the right. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_E6CF27ADD8784D2EAA1770993CE7C0E7" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="CONNECTIVITY" class="- topic/text ">Connectivity </text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-3F57FE8B-9650-49C8-B7A1-011088A61E82" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-06C60694-A471-4723-971B-0AFF8750E5A8-low.png" id="IMAGE_80D3B755DAA74CC694090ACE15C5E307" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-06C60694-A471-4723-971B-0AFF8750E5A8-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_E93FA6391A9F4E74839B67083E85FF86" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_SYSTEM_SETTINGS_CONNECTIVITY_IDENTIFICATION_AND_NETWORK_ADAPTER" class="- topic/text ">Identification and network adapter</text></uicontrol>. You can change the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_PFE265_HOSTNAME.NAME" class="- topic/text ">Hostname</text></uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_PFE_LINKSPEED.NAME" class="- topic/text ">Adapter link speed and duplex mode</text></uicontrol> or <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_PFE311_PRIMARYDNSSUFFIX.NAME" class="- topic/text ">Primary DNS suffix</text></uicontrol>.</ph> 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-DF20E72F-3F83-4C19-AD43-8B248F4D304B" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">You have to log in as System administrator to change the settings. 
</p></note><fig id="FIG_522CA07371334E478CCDF250DE62AC68" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6C31153C-3E6D-49C6-AACD-1EF51D4E3F80-low.png" id="IMAGE_E8800B51319143128AC59DCCD6F97DF7" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6C31153C-3E6D-49C6-AACD-1EF51D4E3F80-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_22247A9D06414A8B944E826CB2FE1069" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_SYSTEM_SETTINGS_CONNECTIVITY_CONNECTIVITY_IPV4" class="- topic/text ">IPv4</text></uicontrol> to change the TCPIP v4 parameters. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_F64508AB884C423CADE3C5CE206E73B2" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_SYSTEM_SETTINGS_CONNECTIVITY_CONNECTIVITY_IPV6" class="- topic/text ">IPv6</text></uicontrol> to change the TCPIP v6 parameters. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_58A7076BA5724CCC8EC4F52BBAF877E9" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><text id="SAVE_BUTTON" class="- topic/text ">Save</text></ph> to save the settings. It is recommended to restart the engine to make sure the settings are activated. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_99750C5BBEA84FE7A37F30DAC5DCF3C6" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="BACK_BUTTON" class="- topic/text ">Back</text></uicontrol> arrow.</ph> 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_3E8AA860BC734F9690D2BD80B98BD758" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="REMOTESERVICE" class="- topic/text ">Remote services</text></uicontrol></ph>. One of the settings you can change are the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="_SYSTEM_SETTINGS_REMOTE_SERVICE_PROXY_SETTINGS" class="- topic/text ">Proxy settings</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-6D4F1059-3AB8-43F8-B297-3DA8E62AAD34" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">A proxy may be required to access the internet and make use of Remote services. Ask your IT administrator for the settings, if he does not know them use the default values. 
</p></note></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_38EBB9AC1C2843DAB029D6313EC317A2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E850A4AB-3196-416C-917A-B65AAF9F0E18-low.png" id="IMAGE_65B939869EC34D25AD177D8F88F6E8A9" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E850A4AB-3196-416C-917A-B65AAF9F0E18-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_0FDE93C48D3247DE85A33C5095F72BBA" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="SAVE_BUTTON" class="- topic/text ">Save</text></uicontrol></ph> to save the settings. 
</cmd></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-663138EA-3A7D-4CB5-BCC8-16CED3251EBA.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
